<HEADLINE> OSU's Redd Announcement Nearing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Ohio State junior Michael Redd will
annouce next week whether he'll make himself available for the NBA
draft, his mother said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   His mother, Haji, said Redd plans to make the announcement
during a news conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   As for the decision, ''That's his news to tell,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   WSYX-TV, citing unnamed sources, said Redd will declare himself
eligible for the draft. But he will not be signing with an agent so
he can withdraw a week before the draft if he doesn't like what
he's hearing on where he will be chosen, the station said.
</P>
<P>
   WBNS-TV and WCMH-TV also reported that Redd had made up his mind
but will not make his intentions known until Tuesday. Those two
stations said Redd's father, James, provided that information.
</P>
<P>
   Redd, 6-foot-6 swingman from Columbus West High School, has
until May 14 to declare his intentions to enter the NBA draft,
which is June 28 in Minneapolis.
</P>
<P>
   Redd averaged 17.3 points and 6.5 rebounds last season for Ohio
State (23-7), which lost to Miami in the second round of the NCAA
South Regional.
</P>
