Heat 97, Raptors 73
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Jamal Mashburn keyed a third-quarter rally that propelled the
Miami Heat to a 97-73 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Tuesday night. Anthony
Carter led the Heat, who never trailed, with 17 points. Mashburn added 16 and
Alonzo Mourning contributed 10 points and four blocks. Vince Carter paced
Toronto with 17 points, Tracy McGrady had 15 and Dee Brown 10.
</P>
