Mavericks 112, Lakers 102
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- Michael Finley scored 25 points as the Dallas Mavericks ended
their 19-game losing streak to the Los Angeles Lakers with a 112-102 victory
Tuesday night. Steve Nash added 23 as Dallas beat the Lakers for the first time
since April 5, 1995. Los Angeles' Shaquille O'Neal led the Lakers with 38 points
and 20 rebounds.
