independent filmmakers who make their movies available over the Internet.
Miramax Films, a unit of the Walt Disney Co., has signed an agreement with
SightSound.com to offer 12 full-length feature films on the Web. The studio's
films include such critical and commercial successes as ''Shakespeare in Love,''
''The Cider House Rules'' and ''Pulp Fiction,'' but the company said Tuesday it
hasn't been decided yet which titles would be made available, how soon or at
what cost.
