<HEADLINE> Dow Down 54; Nasdaq Up 29  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mixed in early trading on
Wednesday. The Dow Jones Industrial Average is down 54 points in
the early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold
a 9-to-8 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 29 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down a fraction.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street has held the bar pretty high for many corporations
this quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts' estimates for corporate earnings have generally been
pretty high. And, for the most part, those who've reported have
managed to exceed the lofty estimates.
</P>
<P>
   But that may not be good enough.
</P>
<P>
   Companies such as America Online, Intel and Lucent all were sent
sharply higher on Tuesday before they released their earnings
reports. They now are likely to lead a bit of a retrenchment on
Wall Street, as the market's ''buy the rumor, sell the news''
phenomenon occurs anew.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
