<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Melina Kanakaredes says the reason behind the success of her NBC
series ''Providence'' may ''have a lot to do with the accessibility
of a family story.'' Kanakaredes, who was born on April 23, 1967,
plays a Los Angeles plastic surgeon who returns home to Providence,
R.I. She told Parade magazine, ''People may not relate to or
understand a doctor story or a police story, but they understand a
family story.''
</P>
<P>
   Al Pacino says movies are OK, but he would rather act on the
stage. ''Movies are wonderful. I love seeing them. But they're not
as much fun to do for me,'' he told the Los Angeles Times. ''It's a
very fragmented existence. You may only shoot a minute a day.''
Pacino, who was born on April 25, 1940, made his Los Angeles
theater debut last summer. He appeared in Eugene O'Neill's
''Hughie'' at the Mark Taper Forum. Pacino played a gambler
chatting with a night clerk (Paul Benedict) at a seedy hotel. The
two won critical praise when they did the show in 1996 in New York.
</P>
<P>
   Last August, tens of thousands of people logged on to watch the
gastric bypass surgery of Carnie Wilson, formerly of the Wilson
Phillips singing trio. During the procedure, the Web site
www.adoctorinyourhouse.com had 2.7 million hits, believed to be
about 50,000 to 200,000 viewers. Wilson, the daughter of Beach Boy
Brian Wilson, said prior to the surgery she was ''morbidly obese''
and the procedure provided a permanent solution to weight loss. She
was born on April 29, 1968.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays for April 23-29:
</P>
<P>
   April 23: Actor Lee Majors (''Six Million Dollar Man'') is 60.
Actress Sandra Dee is 58. Actress Blair Brown is 52. Actress Joyce
DeWitt (''Three's Company'') is 51. Actress Judy Davis is 45.
Actress Jan Hooks is 43. Actress Valerie Bertinelli is 40. Actress
Melina Kanakaredes (''Providence'') is 33. Actor Scott Bairstow is
30.
</P>
<P>
   April 24: Actress Shirley MacLaine is 66. Singer Barbra
Streisand is 58. Actor Michael O'Keefe (''Roseanne'') is 45.
Musician Billy Gould of Faith No More is 37. Musician Patty Schemel
of Hole is 33. Musician Aaron Comess of Spin Doctors is 32.
</P>
<P>
   April 25: Actor Al Pacino is 60. Singer Bjorn Ulvaeus of Abba is
55. Actress Talia Shire is 54. Actor Hank Azaria is 36. Singer Andy
Bell of Erasure is 36. Musician Eric Avery of Jane's Addiction is
35. Actress Rene Zellweger is 31.
</P>
<P>
   April 26: Actress-comedian Carol Burnett is 67.
Musician-songwriter Duane Eddy is 62. Singer Bobby Rydell is 58.
Musician Roger Taylor of Duran Duran is 40. Actor-comedian Kevin
James (''The King of Queens'') is 35. Singer T-Boz of TLC is 30.
Actress Marnette Patterson (''Something So Right'') is 20.
</P>
