<HEADLINE> Kissinger Laments Candidates' Talk  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Henry Kissinger says he's disappointed
that presidential candidates aren't talking more about foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
   ''Things are changing in every part of the world. ... These
events are bound to affect us,'' the former secretary of state
said. ''Distances have shrunk, communication is easier. This
affects our national security.''
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, Americans ''have always felt that we can withdraw
(from world affairs) or involve ourselves at will,'' the Nobel
Peace Prize winner said Tuesday in a speech at the Pasadena Civic
Center.
</P>
</TEXT>
