<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that have been moving substantially or
trading heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq
Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
IBM Corp., down 7[ at 104]
</P>
<P>
   Sales slumped 5 percent in the first quarter, dragged down by a
broad decline in products ranging from desktop computers to
mainframes to hard disk drives. IBM earned $1.52 billion, or 83
cents a share, beating analysts' forecasts of 78 cents a share.
</P>
<P>
America Online Inc., up 1\ at 62
</P>
<P>
   Earnings in the company's fiscal third quarter beat analysts'
expectations by 2 cents a share. The number of subscribers rose,
boosting subscription revenues 33 percent to $1.15 billion.
</P>
<P>
Robert Half International Inc., up 8 7/16 at 57 5/16
</P>
<P>
   The staffing services company earned 47 cents per share in the
first quarter, above analysts' forecasts of 41 cents per share.
Warburg Dillon Read and Dain Rauscher Wessels raised their ratings
on the stock.
</P>
<P>
Aviation Sales Co., down 2 13/16 at 3 11/16
</P>
<P>
   Standard &AMP; Poor's on Tuesday lowered its ratings on Aviation
Sales based on weaker-than-expected operating performance for the
year ended Dec. 31, 1999. The company redistributes aircraft spare
parts and is an independent provider of heavy-maintenance services.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Intel Corp., down 9 15/16 at 119 1/16
</P>
<P>
   First-quarter profits rose 37 percent, and Intel executives
predicted strong sales for the traditionally sluggish second
quarter. But some analysts were looking for higher revenue growth
in the coming quarters. Also, Intel stock rose sharply ahead of the
report, prompting investors to take profits today.
</P>
<P>
Sagent Technology Inc., down 10 29/32 at 7 7/32
</P>
<P>
   The data software company missed its first-quarter revenue and
income targets. Sagent said $3.5 million in contracts didn't
qualify for revenue recognition for the first quarter, and will be
accounted for later this year.
</P>
<P>
Open Market Inc., down 4} at 10[
</P>
<P>
   The company's first-quarter losses exceeded analysts' estimates
by four cents per share. Open Market makes electronic commerce
software. Hoak Breedlove cut its rating on the stock.
</P>
<P>
Interwoven Inc., up 11] at 71 9/16
</P>
<P>
   The company narrowed its losses to 14 cents per share in the
first quarter from $1.47 per share in the first quarter of 1999.
Interwoven provides content-management software.
</P>
</TEXT>
