<HEADLINE> Gore, Bush Positions on Gun Control  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Gun-control positions of Al Gore and George W. Bush:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Both candidates would:
</P>
<P>
   --Support the current ban on assault weapons.
</P>
<P>
   --Prohibit juveniles from possessing assault weapons.
</P>
<P>
   --Ban imports of high-capacity ammunition clips.
</P>
<P>
   --Raise the minimum age for possessing a handgun from 18 to 21.
</P>
<P>
   --Require that trigger locks be sold with handguns.
</P>
<P>
   Gore's also would:
</P>
<P>
   --Require photo licensing for handgun purchases.
</P>
<P>
   --Limit gun sales to one per month and require a three-day
waiting period.
</P>
<P>
   --Require manufacturers and federally licensed sellers to report
sales to a state authority.
</P>
<P>
   Bush also would:
</P>
<P>
   --Provide more money for enforcement.
</P>
<P>
   --Support automatic detention for young people who commit crimes
with guns.
</P>
<P>
   --Oppose government-mandated registration of guns owned by people
who don't break laws.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Bush and Gore campaigns.
</P>
</TEXT>
