<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colgate's 1Q Profit Rises 15 Pct.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Colgate-Palmolive Co.'s first-quarter profit
rose 15 percent, as each of the consumer products company's
divisions around the world showed improvement.
</P>
<P>
   The maker of Colgate toothpaste, Irish Spring soap, Mennen
deodorant and Ajax cleanser earned $239.9 million, or 38 cents a
share, in the three months ended March 31, up from $208.9 million,
or 32 cents a share, a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   That was a penny a share better than analysts surveyed by First
Call/Thomson Financial had expected.
</P>
<P>
   The results reported Wednesday were slightly larger than Wall
Street expectations but Colgate-Palmolive shares fell 43} cents a
share to $55.68} in trading at 4:30 p.m. on the New York Stock
Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   Revenue rose 3 percent to $2.24 billion from $2.18 billion a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
   North American sales were up 5 percent from continuing
businesses as unit volume rose 4 percent. Its Palmolive brand was
the best-selling dishwashing liquid and its Colgate toothpaste
captured a record 43 percent of that market.
</P>
<P>
   Sales climbed 10 percent in Latin America. Sales growth was 4
percent in the Asia-Africa division and 3 percent in the European
division.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
