<HEADLINE> Ad Growth Boosts Meredith Earnings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Advertising growth in its magazines and
other publications helped Meredith Corp. post a 12 percent increase
in earnings for its third fiscal quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Net earnings were $24.8 million, or 47 cents per share, compared
to $22.1 million, or 41 cents per share, a year earlier. Revenues
rose 8 percent to $286.9 million from $265.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   Revenues from Meredith's magazines and other publications,
including Better Homes and Gardens and Successful Farming, were
$224.1 million, up 11 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
   ''Of special note is Ladies' Home Journal magazine. It achieved
marked improvement in the third quarter, with advertising pages up
8 percent versus the prior year, and even stronger advertising
revenue growth,'' said William T. Kerr, Meredith chairman and chief
executive.
</P>
<P>
   Revenues from Meredith's broadcasting group, however, slipped to
$62.9 million from $63.1 million a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Kerr blamed, among other things, investments in the Atlanta
station WGNX-TV, news expansion across the group and low prime-time
ratings for the Fox network. Six of Meredith's 12 stations are Fox
affiliates.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Meredith were priced at $27.25 at 5:15 p.m. EST on the
New York Stock Exchange, up 50 cents or about 2 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
