<HEADLINE> United Technologies' Earnings Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- United Technologies Corp.'s earnings rose
22 percent in the first quarter, boosted by strong revenue growth
at its Carrier building systems, Otis elevators and Flight Systems
units.
</P>
<P>
   United Technologies earned $377 million, or 74 cents per share,
compared with $308 million, or 63 cents per share, in the same
period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Revenues increased 17 percent in the quarter to $6.39 billion,
compared with $5.44 billion a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   At Carrier, UTC's heating, air-conditioning and refrigeration
unit, operating profit rose 35 percent to $123 million, helped by
strong performance in North America. Revenues at UTC increased 22
percent to $1.85 billion, partly due to recent acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
   During the quarter, Carrier acquired Electrolux's commercial
refrigeration business for $140 million. With annual sales of more
than $300 million, the acquisition doubles Carrier's European
commercial refrigeration operations.
</P>
<P>
   The elevator maker, Otis, had a 13 percent increase in revenues.
</P>
<P>
   At Pratt &AMP; Whitney, UTC's jet-engine unit, operating profit
inched up 1 percent to $282 million on 10 percent lower revenues as
declines in large military and commercial engine shipments were
offset by growth in Canada operations and continued cost cuts.
</P>
<P>
   In the Flight Systems segment, operating profit tripled to $138
million as revenues more than doubled from the inclusion of the
recently acquired Sundstrand's operations and higher value
helicopter shipments at Sikorsky.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of United Technologies rose $3.06\, or 5 percent, to
$61.12{ in trading at 4:30 p.m. on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
