<HEADLINE> Blair Briefs Clinton on Russia Talks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton was briefed Wednesday by
British Prime Minister Tony Blair on his talks with Vladimir Putin
on his first visit to the West as Russia's president.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton and Blair talked by telephone for 35 minutes, delaying
Clinton's departure for Oklahoma City for a memorial ceremony on
the fifth anniversary of the terrorist explosion that killed 168
people.
</P>
<P>
   The two leaders discussed Russia's economic problems, White
House press secretary Joe Lockhart said. They also discussed
Northern Ireland and the violence in Zimbabwe by black squatters on
white-owned farms.
</P>
<P>
   Putin met with Blair in London Monday, promising to seek
friendlier ties with Europe. Blair responded by saying Putin
''talks our language on reform.''
</P>
</TEXT>
