<HEADLINE> Newark makes arrest in 1991 murder case  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- The police department's Cold Case Squad has
solved a 1991 murder case that was reopened a month ago.
</P>
<P>
   Police arrested Major Sheffield, 33, of Newark on Monday and
charged him with the 1991 beating death of Willie Orr.
</P>
<P>
   The case dated back to Sept. 6, 1991 when Orr was walking in
front of a house on South 18th Street when he accidentally bumped
into some children who were playing in front of it.
</P>
<P>
   As one of the children fell to the ground, a man ran up to Orr
and chased him into a nearby alley, where he beat him with his
fists.
</P>
<P>
   Orr staggered into a nearby apartment, collapsed and never
regained consciousness. He died later at University Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Despite an initial investigation by the department's homicide
unit, the case remained unsolved.
</P>
<P>
   On March 17, detectives Keith Sheppard and Rashid Sabur decided
to reopen the case, and developed information that led to
Sheffield's arrest.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Cold Case Squad has been instrumental in bringing closure
for the families of victims,'' said Police Director Joseph
Santiago. ''Detectives Sheppard and Sabur have established that the
Newark Police Department will pursue all leads to solve a crime.''
</P>
</TEXT>
