points to 19,001.29 points in early trading. In New York on Wednesday, the Dow
Jones industrial average fell 92.46 points to close at 10,674.96. The Nasdaq
composite index closed at 3,706.41, down 87.16.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Bucks' Allen Plays 296th Game
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Despite a sprained knee, the Milwaukee Bucks' Ray Allen
suited up and extended his consecutive games streak to 296 -- every one in his
four-year NBA career. Allen sprained his left knee in the Bucks'
playoff-clinching victory over the Orlando Magic on Monday night. After a day of
tests and rehabilitation, Allen decided to play in Milwaukee's finale against
the Washington Wizards. It has been a breakout season for Allen, whose personal
growth into a budding superstar has mirrored Milwaukee's climb to
respectability.
AP NewsBrief by LISI de BOURBON 
