<HEADLINE> 6 Guatemala Crash Victims Found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- Authorities on Wednesday pulled six bodies
from the wreckage of a small plane that went down in northwest
Guatemala earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
   All were representatives of the Wings of Hope Christian
Association, a humanitarian group based in Mayaland in the
northwestern state of Quiche.
</P>
<P>
   The group left Monday morning in a Cessna single-engine plane
for Huehuetenango, about 78 miles northwest of Guatemala City, on a
humanitarian mission. The pilot later dropped out of radio contact.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said they expect to release the identities of all
the victims early next week.
</P>
