<HEADLINE> Fusion 2, Haiti 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Diego Serna scored on a penalty
kick in the 76th minute Wednesday night, providing the difference
as the Miami Fusion beat the Haitian national team 2-1 in an
exhibition soccer game.
</P>
<P>
   The penalty kick was set up after Fusion forward Welton was
fouled by Haitian defender Roosevelt Desirt inside the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
   After a scoreless first half, Haiti took a 1-0 lead in the 61st
minute on Frantz Gilles' goal. Gilles received a pass from Vladimir
Edouard and drilled a 12-yard shot inside the left post past goalie
Garth Lagerwey.
</P>
