<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mavericks 113, Timberwolves 107  </HEADLINE>
By ARNIE STAPLETON, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Steve Nash had 22 points and 10 assists as
the Dallas Mavericks beat the shorthanded Minnesota Timberwolves
113-107 Wednesday night for their 11th win in their final 13 games.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Finley added 18 points and Erick Strickland and Cedric
Ceballos each scored 17 for the Mavericks, who closed the season
with a flourish. After falling 14 games below .500 on Jan. 10, the
Mavericks (40-42) went 30-18.
</P>
<P>
   The Wolves, who finished 50-32 for the best record in franchise
history, already had turned their attention to their first-round
playoff series with Portland.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm not taking anything away from Dallas, because right now
they're playing as well as anybody,'' Wolves coach Flip Saunders
said before the game. ''But the last two days, our staff has spent
all our time watching Portland. I'm going to start calling them
Portland.''
</P>
<P>
   At times, the Mavericks looked like a playoff team, thanks to
Minnesota's depleted lineup.
</P>
<P>
   With the sixth seed in the Western Conference secured, Kevin
Garnett (hamstring) and Terrell Brandon (back) watched the game in
street clothes.
</P>
<P>
   Brandon was placed on the injured list, and the Wolves activated
forward Andrae Patterson. Brandon will be back for the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   Garnett, who missed a game for the first time all season, became
the ninth player in NBA history to average 20 points, 10 rebounds
and five assists. The last one to do it was Charles Barkley for
Phoenix in 1992-93.
</P>
<P>
   Anthony Peeler scored a season-high 22 points and Bobby Jackson
tied his season-high with 21 for Minnesota. Wally Szczerbiak added
19.
</P>
<P>
   Szczerbiak's 3-pointer with 35 seconds left in the third quarter
gave the Wolves their biggest lead, 87-80. But the Mavericks went
on a 14-2 run, capped by Strickland's three-point play, for a 94-89
lead. Dallas never trailed again.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Saunders said that if Dallas' Don Nelson has coached his
last game, ''he's put this team in the right direction.'' ... The
Mavericks made their first 16 free throws. ... Patterson spent
almost all season on the injured list after tearing cartilage on
Oct. 28 and undergoing an operation the next day. ... Other players
who have averaged 20 points, 10 boards and five assists are: Larry
Bird, Wilt Chamberlain, Elgin Baylor, Oscar Robertson, Kareem
Abdul-Jabbar, Billy Cunningham and Sidney Wicks. ... Brandon missed
11 games this season with a variety of ailments.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
