<HEADLINE> Pakistan Mine Explosion Kills 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) -- A coal mine explosion in southwestern
Pakistan killed seven workers and injured another 13, the state-run
news agency said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The explosion late Wednesday in southwestern Baluchistan was
caused by a build up of methane gas, according to The Associated
Press of Pakistan, which quoted Ghulam Sarwar Lodhi, Pakistan's
chief inspector of mines.
</P>
<P>
   A three-hour rescue operation freed 13 workers, who were taken
to hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The mine was closed and Lodhi ordered an investigation into the
accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
