<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 22:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Editors Take Over Sun-Times  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- The top editors at two Canadian newspapers will
take over leadership of the Chicago Sun-Times next month, the
newspaper said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Sun-Times Editor in Chief Nigel Wade will be succeeded by
Michael Cooke, editor in chief of The Vancouver Province for the
last five years.
</P>
<P>
   John Cruickshank, editor in chief of The Vancouver Sun, will
become the Sun-Times' vice president of editorial.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun-Times and the Vancouver newspapers are owned by
Hollinger International Inc., a newspaper group owned by Canadian
Conrad M. Black.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have enjoyed 37 demanding years of daily journalism, but I
have other private goals I would like to achieve,'' Wade said in a
statement. He will step down May 15.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
