<HEADLINE> 7 Guatemala Crash Victims Found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- Authorities late Wednesday pulled a
seventh body from the wreckage of a small plane that went down in
northwest Guatemala earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
   Six other bodies were recovered earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
   All were representatives of the Wings of Hope Christian
Association, a humanitarian group based in Mayaland in the
northwestern state of Quiche. Officials said at least one foreigner
was aboard, but they said they would not give the person's
nationality until Thursday when the victims' identities are to be
released.
</P>
<P>
   The group left Monday morning in a Cessna single-engine plane
for Huehuetenango, about 78 miles northwest of Guatemala City, on a
humanitarian mission. The pilot later dropped out of radio contact.
</P>
